crow's nest
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:a platform in a cabbage tree or on poles, used as a lookout for boundary keeping purposes [prior to fencing].
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Flag: Farm Words
Domain:Rural
Region:[none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes:
Citations
Date: 7/10/1933
Source: Press, The
Author:
Vol / Page: 15
Edition:
Quote: Platform built on poles or in a cabbage tree from which a shepherd could see his sheep. <i>C[row's] n[est]s</i> were used on the old plains stations until the runs were fenced about 1860. ([ca1890-1910].)
Notes: (Acland Gloss.)

