Source: Sheep and Sheepmen of Canterbury
Author: CRAWFORD
Vol / Page: 39
Edition:
Quote: In order to disturb the sheep as little as possible ... `crows nests', platforms on poles or in cabbage trees, were frequently built on the plains as look-out stations [for boundary keepers].
